  "original_title": "Payment to be made today to bring down petrol shipment between July 13 and 15: Minister",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Payment to be made today to bring down petrol shipment between July 13 and 15: Minister",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "An advanced payment would be made today to bring down a petrol shipment between July 13,14 and 15 , earlier than the scheduled shipment which is expected by July 22, Power and Energy Minister Kanchana Wijesekara said today.",
        "He told Parliament that proposals were called from suppliers to bring down a petrol shipment between July 10 and 15 but only one supplier offered bids but it was at higher prices.",
        "\"Malasian Company had said they will supply a petrol shipment between July 10 and 15. But, they could not confirm the date. There is another supplier who has offered to supply a petrol shipment between July 13 and 15. But, we will have to pay higher prices for that. We can bring it down if you all agree for that. Unless we purchase this shipment, we will have to wait till July 22,\" he said.",
        "The Minister said some factions had objected to purchasing this shipment at higher prices misleading the people that it was done to get commissions and added that the decision was taken at a technicle committee with the Cabinet approval. \"The President and the Prime Minister also instrcuted me to purchase this shipment which will be due between July 13 and 15 without waiting till July 22.We will make the advanced payment of USD 26 million for that shipment today. If there is any boubt on the procedure, please, do not disturb now and question the procedure at the COPE or COPA,\" he said.",
        "He said this in response to a question raised by NPP MP Vijitha Herath from the Prime Minister. (Ajith Siriwardana and Yohan Perera)"
      ],
